snippet.textDisplay: Mac's music has helped me through some of the hardest times in my life. It always seemed like every time he released an album, I was experiencing similar things in my life and it was as if he was speaking directly to me. As his music got a little darker, so did my life and I fell further into depression/drug abuse. His music meant the world to me and even though he never even knew I existed, it was as if he was my closest friend at times. Anyways, on January 15th of this year, my fiance passed away completely unexpectedly from complications with her cancer. That girl was my entire world. She literally saved my life. I could go on for weeks about her. Since she passed I've been beyond lost and I know I'll never get over this. 2 days after she passed, circles was released and I've had it on repeat since. Although I'm still hurting more than I knew possible, the album brings me so much peace/comfort at times. Its hard to explain. I'm so thankful for Mac and all the beautiful art he shared with us. Rest in piece brother, you are missed dearly ❤
snippet.textOriginal: Mac's music has helped me through some of the hardest times in my life. It always seemed like every time he released an album, I was experiencing similar things in my life and it was as if he was speaking directly to me. As his music got a little darker, so did my life and I fell further into depression/drug abuse. His music meant the world to me and even though he never even knew I existed, it was as if he was my closest friend at times. Anyways, on January 15th of this year, my fiance passed away completely unexpectedly from complications with her cancer. That girl was my entire world. She literally saved my life. I could go on for weeks about her. Since she passed I've been beyond lost and I know I'll never get over this. 2 days after she passed, circles was released and I've had it on repeat since. Although I'm still hurting more than I knew possible, the album brings me so much peace/comfort at times. Its hard to explain. I'm so thankful for Mac and all the beautiful art he shared with us. Rest in piece brother, you are missed dearly ❤
